#compdef mbtileserver
# =============================================================================
# mbtileserver — Conservation Biology Institute's "Basic Go
#                server for mbtiles" — a Go HTTP server for
#                MBTiles (SQLite-packaged map tile databases)
#                serving raster + vector tiles for
#                cartographic frontends (Mapbox GL JS, MapLibre
#                GL JS, Leaflet, OpenLayers, ArcGIS).
#                Distinguishing from tileserver-gl, t-rex,
#                pg_tileserv, and other tile servers by:
#                  - MBTILES NATIVE — reads SQLite-packaged
#                    MBTiles 1.3 spec files (the OGC standard
#                    for tile distribution); supports raster
#                    (PNG / JPEG / WEBP) + vector tiles (PBF /
#                    MVT)
#                  - DIRECTORY-SCANNED TILESETS — serves all
#                    .mbtiles files in --dir (default
#                    ./tilesets/); URL paths derived from
#                    relative paths
#                  - TILEJSON + ArcGIS MapServer ENDPOINTS —
#                    publishes TileJSON 3.0 metadata
#                    automatically; ArcGIS MapServer endpoints
#                    for compatibility with Esri tools
#                    (via --enable-arcgis)
#                  - PREVIEW PAGE — built-in interactive
#                    Mapbox-GL-JS preview at /services/<id>/
#                    map for visual inspection
#                  - HMAC AUTHENTICATION via --secret-key —
#                    HMAC-signed URLs for time-limited
#                    authenticated tile access
#                  - AUTO TLS via Let's Encrypt — `--tls`
#                    enables ACME-based certificate
#                    provisioning + renewal via
#                    golang.org/x/crypto/acme/autocert
#                  - SENTRY ERROR REPORTING via --dsn
#                  - HOT-RELOAD VIA TWO MODES:
#                      * --enable-reload-signal: SIGHUP
#                        triggers graceful child-process
#                        restart (supervisor pattern)
#                      * --enable-fs-watch: fsnotify-based
#                        filesystem watcher detects MBTiles
#                        file additions / modifications /
#                        removals / renames and dynamically
#                        registers / unregisters tilesets
#                        WITHOUT process restart
#                  - SHARED-LIBRARY MBTILES READING via
#                    brendan-ward/mbtiles-go — Cgo-free SQLite
#                    binding for read-only MBTiles access
#                  - ECHO HTTP FRAMEWORK — labstack/echo v4 for
#                    routing + middleware
#                Used by: cartography teams hosting custom
#                Mapbox-style raster + vector tile services,
#                offline-first mapping deployments, and as a
#                reference implementation of fsnotify +
#                spf13/cobra + labstack/echo + autocert
#                composition in Go.
#
# Author:  Conservation Biology Institute (consbio.org) —
#          Bend, Oregon-based environmental research nonprofit.
#          mbtileserver maintained by Brendan Ward + CBI
#          engineering team.  Released ~2017; active
#          development through 2026.  License: ISC.
# Source:  https://github.com/consbio/mbtileserver
#          https://github.com/consbio/mbtileserver/blob/master/main.go
#          https://github.com/consbio/mbtileserver/blob/master/watch.go
#          https://github.com/consbio/mbtileserver/blob/master/go.mod
# CLI:     main.go — uses spf13/cobra (well-documented
#          elsewhere).  Headline library: **fsnotify/fsnotify**
#          (cobra is documented across hundreds of Go completions;
#          fsnotify is the new variant being documented here,
#          expanding Axis 17 — File Watching — to Go).
# Library: github.com/fsnotify/fsnotify v1.8.0
#          ("fsnotify" — "Cross-platform filesystem
#           notifications for Go" — multi-maintainer group
#           (originally by Chris Howey + Nathan Youngman; now
#           community-maintained under fsnotify org).
#           Distinct from notify (R653, Rust Axis 17 opener)
#           by being:
#              1. CROSS-PLATFORM via kernel APIs — single Go
#                 abstraction over:
#                   * Linux:   inotify (kernel 2.6.13+)
#                   * macOS:   FSEvents + kqueue
#                   * Windows: ReadDirectoryChangesW
#                   * BSDs:    kqueue
#                   * Solaris: FEN (File Events Notification)
#                 fsnotify.NewWatcher() returns a Watcher
#                 wired to the platform's native backend.
#              2. CHANNEL-FIRST DESIGN — Watcher has two
#                 channels:
#                   watcher.Events <-chan fsnotify.Event
#                   watcher.Errors <-chan error
#                 Idiomatic Go select{} consumes both:
#                   for {
#                     select {
#                     case ev := <-watcher.Events:
#                       handle(ev)
#                     case err := <-watcher.Errors:
#                       log.Printf("watch err: %v", err)
#                     }
#                   }
#              3. BIT-FLAG OPERATIONS — fsnotify.Op is a
#                 bitmask (Create | Write | Remove | Rename |
#                 Chmod):
#                   if ev.Op&fsnotify.Create == fsnotify.Create
#                   if ev.Op&fsnotify.Write  == fsnotify.Write
#                 Each event reports ALL applicable operations
#                 in one Event value (vs notify's discrete
#                 EventKind enum).
#              4. SIMPLER API — Watcher.Add(path) / Remove(path);
#                 no Recursive flag (you manually walk
#                 directories and call Add for each).  Distinct
#                 from notify's RecursiveMode flag.
#              5. STABLE v1 API SINCE 2014 — fsnotify is one
#                 of the most-stable Go libraries; v1.0 since
#                 2014, minimal API breakage; v1.8.0 in 2026.
#              6. PROMOTED INTO GO ECOSYSTEM CANON — fsnotify
#                 is so widely used that "use fsnotify" is
#                 the de facto Go solution for filesystem
#                 watching; appears in the Awesome Go list,
#                 used by viper (Steve Francia) for config
#                 hot-reload, air (cosmtrek) for Go hot-reload,
#                 tilt (Tilt Dev) for Kubernetes dev loops,
#                 etc.
#              7. PURE GO — no Cgo dependencies; inotify /
#                 FSEvents / ReadDirectoryChangesW / kqueue
#                 accessed via syscall package.
#              8. DEBOUNCED-EVENT GUIDANCE — fsnotify
#                 README documents the well-known "editor
#                 saves emit multiple Write events" caveat
#                 and how to debounce; library remains
#                 unopinionated.
#              9. NO RECURSIVE-WATCH IN CORE — by design,
#                 fsnotify does not abstract recursive
#                 watching (separate fsnotify-rs, fsnotify
#                 supplementary packages provide this).
#                 Distinct from notify's RecursiveMode.
#             10. FSNOTIFY-ORG / COMMUNITY-MAINTAINED — moved
#                 from howeyc/fsnotify to fsnotify/fsnotify
#                 under a community org in 2016; now multi-
#                 maintainer.)
