#
#   Axis 17 (FILE WATCHING) variants:
#     - notify (notify-rs/notify) — R653 (_tobaru) — Rust
#       cross-platform; inotify (Linux) + FSEvents (macOS) +
#       ReadDirectoryChangesW (Windows) + kqueue (BSD);
#       François Mockers / notify-rs ecosystem
#     - fsnotify (fsnotify/fsnotify) — R654 (THIS) — Go cross-
#       platform; same kernel APIs + Solaris FEN; channel-first
#       Go-idiomatic API; bit-flag Op; community-maintained
#       under fsnotify/fsnotify
#
# Two Axis 17 variants address SUBTLY DIFFERENT API designs:
#   notify             = ENUM-based EventKind with subkinds +
#                         RecursiveMode flag (Rust)
#   fsnotify           = BIT-FLAG Op (Create|Write|Remove|
#                         Rename|Chmod) + channel-based +
#                         non-recursive by default (Go)
#
# Both libraries wrap THE SAME platform kernel APIs (inotify,
# FSEvents, ReadDirectoryChangesW, kqueue), differing primarily
# in the language-idiomatic API shape:
#   - Rust notify:    EventKind enum + closure/channel +
#                      RecursiveMode + DebouncedWatcher variant
#   - Go fsnotify:    Op bitmask + select-friendly channels +
#                      no built-in recursion + no debouncer
#
# Axis 17 distribution: Rust=1, Go=1, TS-Node=0.  Expected R655
# TS-Node=1 (likely chokidar) restores three-language symmetry
# trajectory.
